								<p>Every College needs a voice and Apostle of Speech embodies the voice of CCET. Built upon its motto - Silence Unjustified, AOS has left a grand mark on the local and national literary scene. It has been an institution for developing acumen in not just public speaking but also areas like critical thinking, logic, Idea framing and leadership. Love and appreciation of literature and creativity is also at the core of the group.</p>
								<p>To achieve excellence in all these fields, members of the club organise and participate in workshops for Group Discussions, Debates, Creative writing, Quizzing and logical reasoning. Understanding that fun should be in the heart of every club, AOS also hosts fun events like Just A Minute (JAM) and poetry slam. It has the distinction of being one of the very few literary clubs in the country to organise a National Parliamentary Debate Tournament by the name of Evince. </p>
								<p>The club has seen tremendous success over the years. It has represented college at prestigious events like Indian National Debate Championship ( INDC), IITD-PD, Trivium, NH 65-PD among others. It’s members have also bagged multiple wins in various events at Rendezvous (IIT Delhi), Zeitgeist (IIT Ropar), Pecfest, Verve (PEC), Goonj(UIET), Cyanide(UICET) and Apratim(CCET)</p>
